-- Brentford Dumps Everton From League Cup Soccer; Arsenal Defeats Spurs 4-1
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2010-09-21T23:03:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/brentford-dumps-everton-from-league-cup-soccer-arsenal-defeats-spurs-4-1.html
Brentford, which plays in English
soccer’s third tier, knocked Premier League club Everton out of
the League Cup on penalty kicks in the biggest upset of last
night’s third-round matches.  Brentford, which is in 19th place in League One, won the
shootout 4-3 after the game in London finished 1-1 after extra
time.  Jermaine Beckford  and  Phil Jagielka  missed their spot
kicks for Everton.  Samir Nasri  struck two penalties in extra time as Arsenal
won 4-1 at Tottenham. The north London rivals were tied 1-1
after 90 minutes following goals by Arsenal’s Henri Lansbury and
Spurs striker  Robbie Keane .  Andrey Arshavin  added the Gunners’
fourth.  Burnley, demoted to the second-tier Championship last
season, beat Premier League club Bolton 1-0 on Wade Elliott’s
45th-minute volley. Stoke defeated Fulham 2-0 with goals from
Danny Higginbotham and Kenwyne Jones, while West Ham won 2-1 at
Sunderland in another all-Premier League matchup.  Wolverhampton Wanderers, Birmingham, Ipswich, Swansea and
Leicester also advanced last night.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  